Ringtail Icons

Application design relies heavily on icons. As I created more and more icons for single projects it became difficult to keep up with them. I also wanted an easy way to swap one out when I needed to change the meaning of someting (like a download vs. view button). The solution was to create my own icon font. Because all of the icons are in one place (and I added a bunch), we can easily drop a few files into our web projects and have our own custom icon library.

I’ve made the font available as a free download. Feel free to use it in your own projects.

Over time, I realized that using an icon font came with a couple of small headaches, so recently I’ve been exploring SVG. Feel free to grab those too if it helps you.
